# What survives git here (Battlewrath), and what doesn't:
#   Docket_complete/            TRACKED - the .txt import strings + register.jsonl are durable PRODUCTS, expensive to
#                               regenerate. This is what "don't reproduce 1000 files" means.
#   Docket_stage/*.docket.json  TRACKED - the staged dockets survive so we don't repeat the staging work.
#   *.gate.json                 IGNORED - per-docket gate stubs are EPHEMERAL by design (a per-run verdict, not a keeper).
#   receipts/                   IGNORED - verbose per-run execution logs; the survivable run-log is Docket_complete/register.jsonl.
receipts/
*.gate.json
